    "story":  [
                  "At the very summit, \u003cb\u003eQuince\u003c/b\u003e is grinding out 4 clean sheets like a man morally opposed to fun \u0026mdash; ugly, effective, and a touch boring. Hot on their heels, \u003cb\u003eEllie\u003c/b\u003e is the undisputed sultan of the stalemate: 5 draws and counting. Edge-of-the-seat stuff it is not. Rounding out the smug end of the table, \u003cb\u003eBig Pewerk\u003c/b\u003e bagged the pasting of the tournament so far, Netherlands (beautiful football, then a fistfight among themselves) romping home 5-1. Borderline rude.",
                  "Wading into the midtable swamp, \u003cb\u003eSid\u003c/b\u003e is hauling Türkiye (100% passion, 100% chaos, 0% chill) around like a dead fridge up a fire escape \u0026mdash; it\u0027s played, and contributed the square root of sod all. Keeping them grim company, \u003cb\u003eElsa\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s backline has the structural integrity of a wet paper bag \u0026mdash; 19 shipped already, with Tunisia (stubborn, organised, impossible to love) alone waving in 9. And clinging on by their fingernails, \u003cb\u003eEtan\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s lot have collectively decided defending is for cowards \u0026mdash; 11 goals banged in (GD -6), spearheaded by England (bravely marching toward an inevitable penalty heartbreak).",
                  "Down in the cheap seats, \u003cb\u003eMurray\u003c/b\u003e is simply... there \u0026mdash; 10 pts from 10 games (2W 4D 4L), the beige wallpaper of the leaderboard. And scraping the very bottom of the barrel, \u003cb\u003eIke\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s pride and joy is a tidy 3-1 spanking from France (world-beaters one dressing-room row from civil war) \u0026mdash; ruthless, efficient, faintly smug."
              ],
